Of recent, the compulsive educationist and gregarious Ayo Ogunsan was appointed as a member of the advisory board of the United Kingdomâ€™s Wolver Hampton University; it was an eloquent testimony of his avowed commitment to the uplifting of education on all fronts. This man of near impeccable character has been in the vanguard of imparting knowledge in the younger folks, even when he was a young chap, and he has not looked back. Ayo is also an advisory board member of Caleb University; and to boot, the dynamic and resourceful founding and executive member of the Lagos State Security Trust Fund and with this new cap, he is still inching high, higher and even highest to attain more lofty heights and the sky seems to be his starting point. Enigmatic Ayo Ogunsan will sure continue to be a recurring decimal in the advancement of education, all things being equal. He is a graduate of Business Administration from the prestigious Yaba College of Technology and Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti. He also holds membership of the Institute of Directors of Nigeria (IoD). He is also a member of the Nigerian-Britain Association; a member, of the Nigerian-British Chamber of Commerce; a member, the Nigerian-American Chamber of Commerce; member, Nigerian-Spanish Association. Ogunsan has bagged numerous degrees and certifications from citadels of learning, locally and internationally, including Lagos Business School, Oxford Brookes University and Harvard University, US. Debonair Ayo Ogunsan is a serial entrepreneur with a proven track record in sales administration, financing, investment development, training, security and project management. Sitting atop a conglomerate called the Executive Group, his chain of businesses includes Executive Motors Limited, Executive Voyage and Logistics, Executive Trainers and Executive Education Consulting Limited. The group is primarily into automobiles sales and services with a focus on the Peugeot brand.